      "content": "You are absolutely right to be concerned about the microbiome, but stopping antibiotics early is the single biggest cause of antibiotic resistance, which makes future infections much harder to treat. Your gut bacteria will naturally recover on its own once you stop the medication, and the risk of the infection returning or becoming resistant far outweighs the temporary disruption to your microbiome. Please finish the full course exactly as prescribed, and if you have lingering anxiety about side effects, discuss probiotics with your doctor instead of cutting the dose.",
